This paper deals with computational geometry and algorithms for computing Voronoi diagrams, which are typically studied in the cs.CG (Computational Geometry) sub-category. The paper also discusses structural properties of the diagram, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The use of polygonal sites and the complexity analysis suggest that cs.GR (Graphics) could also be a relevant sub-category. Finally, the mention of "farthest-site" suggests that the paper could be related to optimization or control theory, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control).
